text: President Trump said he’s “heard” that Sen. Kamala Harris may not “meet the requirements” to appear on the Democratic presidential ticket and vowed to “take a look” at the claim when someone asked him if Harris is somehow not a natural-born citizen https://t.co/eTERX7i97Z

name: thedailybeast
text: Asked about the baseless claim that Harris is somehow not a natural-born citizen, the president ran with it: “I heard it today that she doesn’t meet the requirements, and by the way the lawyer who wrote the piece is highly qualified, very talented.” https://t.co/OJjNIbSpTr

name: thedailybeast
text:
Phoebe Robinson of “2 Dope Queens” has never seen the very white ’90s sitcom “Frasier,” but she named her new advice podcast “Black Frasier” anyway.

“I saw some screenshots and I was like, I get it,” @dopequeenpheebs says. https://t.co/svP22Y3jQq

name: thedailybeast
text:
Robinson tells #TheLastLaugh podcast she’s writing a new book called “Six Feet Apart.” 

She's also working on her upcoming Comedy Central talk show, “Doing the Most,” which is about her… doing the most (and learning new life skills while she’s at it!). https://t.co/svP22Y3jQq

name: thedailybeast
text: “I always call myself a low-budget Oprah,” Robinson adds. “So this is like my Nordstrom Rack version of like a Super Soul Sunday moment, with more dick jokes.” https://t.co/svP22Y3jQq

name: thedailybeast
text:
Funnily enough, the best advice Robinson has ever received was from a former assistant, who told her to stop... doing the most.

“She said to me, if you said yes to fewer things, you would actually be a more productive person.” https://t.co/svP22Y3jQq

name: thedailybeast
text: NEW: President Trump didn’t have a lot to say about Joe Biden's VP pick Kamala Harris during the Dem primary, but there was one thing that has stayed on his mind all this time: her support for having him criminally prosecuted once he’s no longer in power https://t.co/1dZ6eJI2QZ

name: thedailybeast
text:
Trump made a point of trashing Harris for saying that based on the Mueller report findings the DOJ would have “no choice” but to pursue obstruction of justice charges against him.

“I’ve seen prosecution of cases based on much less evidence,” Harris said. https://t.co/1dZ6eJI2QZ

name: thedailybeast
text: Another source said Trump had jokingly accused Harris of “ripping him off” by “swapping in ‘Lock Him Up’ in place of ‘Lock Her Up,’” Trump’s longtime anti-Hillary Clinton rallying cry https://t.co/1dZ6eJI2QZ

name: thedailybeast
text:
But current and former attorneys for the president find the idea laughable.

“Criminal prosecution of President Trump? [Kamala] must be smoking something,” John Dowd, a lawyer who represented Trump for nearly a year during the Russia probe, said. https://t.co/1dZ6eJI2QZ
